Key Match Events: Travis Head helped blast Australia to T20 liftoff against inexperienced England
Pre-Game Insights: England win the toss and bowl first
Australia’s captain, Mitch Marsh, mentioned the team was on par for above 200
England’s skipper, Phil Salt, mentioned the team needed 50 off 30 but were just a few wickets down
Guy Hornsby praised Adil Rashid for his control and variety
Post-Match Reflections: Mitch Marsh acknowledged the team played extremely well and the bowlers dragged it back
Phil Salt mentioned the team played well but needed to chase 50 off 30 with fewer wickets down
Travis Head expressed disappointment not to go on with his innings but set a platform
Adil Rashid claimed 2-23 from his four overs and was praised for his control and variety
Miscellaneous Highlights: Every Aussie bowler bagged a wicket
England’s Saqib Mahmood crunched a six off the first ball by standing tall and whacking a shortish ball over midwicket
Matthew Short took a catch to dismiss England’s Phil Salt
Tim David took a stunning catch to dismiss England’s Jordan Cox
Xavier Bartlett was dismissed by Jofra Archer with a full, straight, fast delivery
Josh Inglis was dismissed by Sam Curran with a slower ball
Cameron Green was dismissed by Saqib Mahmood with a yorker
The final score for Australia was 179-9
The final score for England was 151-9
